url: "https://github.com/swanand-tanavade/iort-dt"
abstract: >-
  IoRT-DT (Internet of Robotic Things — Digital Twins) is an open-source federated
  digital twin framework for autonomous underwater vehicle (AUV) fleets. It implements
  four research contributions: (1) acoustic-constrained DT synchronization with
  information-theoretic bounds (RQ1), (2) gossip-based federated DT coordination with
  partition tolerance (RQ2), (3) physics-informed anomaly detection using CUSUM and
  Shiryaev-Roberts detectors with formal ARL guarantees (RQ3), and (4) DDS/SROS2
  security hardening for acoustic channel constraints (RQ4). Built on ROS 2 Jazzy,
  Stonefish simulator, and Zenoh middleware.
